 is also part of a wider context that incites us to fully consider the ways in which histories are performed, called upon, staged, told, imagined, and interpreted. Stories of Oka: Land, Film, and Literature examines the standoff in relation to film and literary narratives, both Indigenous and non-Indigenous. This new English edition of St-Amand’s interdisciplinary, intercultural, and multi-perspective work offers a framework for thinking through the relationships that both unite and oppose settler societies and Indigenous peoples in Canada.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMohawk IndianszQuébec (Province)zKanesatake Indian ReservexClaims. 0aMohawk IndianszQuébec (Province)zKanesatake Indian ReservexGovernment relations. 0aMohawk IndianszQuébec (Province)zKanesatake Indian ReservexClaims. 0aMohawk IndianszQuébec (Province)zKanesatake Indian ReservexGovernment relations. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / Native American Studies.2bisacsh1 aDavid Cree, Katsitsén: hawe Linda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavid Cree, Katsitsén:hawe Linda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStewart, S.E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311127363108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018z978311127598740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978088755552740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780887555527423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780887555527/original  a978-3-11-127363-1  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-127598-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles